<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum72/HTML/000036.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ping Lo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Has any work begun on creating a document on the origins of the monsters of dereth?<P>For example: it's common knowledge that drudges, banderlings, mosswarts, and tumeroks all came from the same world.<P>I got to thinking about this when examining a Shreth; a monster that now inhabits many regions of dereth.  It appears to be distantly related to the Tusker, which were brought to dereth by the Virindi.  Perhaps there is significance to the appearance of the Shreths.<P><BR>Ping Lo </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ethos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ping! Great to see you here, been a while since pre-beta when I was one of your goons  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/ubb/smile.gif"> (ie. a low level vassal).<P>If you'd like to submit information on this, it would be greatly appreciated. We'll certainly credit you as the source of any knowledge on this subject. If you do the write up yourself, I'll consider you a contributing member of the History staff in the Lore section staff credits.<P>------------------<BR>Ethos<BR>Senior Editor<BR>AC Stratics<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Raze</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I would be interested in doing monsters history....<P>------------------<BR>Raze The Lone<BR>Traveller<BR>----------<BR>To Seek is<BR>not to find yet<BR>to not is to find...<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Stormwaltz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">MS is going to be posting a series of writeups on the activities and origins of the more common monsters (i.e. don't expect stuff on the Virindi or Sclavus). They probably won't get into that much detail, at least inferrring from the fact that the Drudge writeup I did for them was judged "a bit long," but struck me as only barely sufficient.<P>BTW, Tumeroks aren't from the same place as Drudges, Banderlings, and Mosswarts. Their original habitat can be inferred by their current places of residence and coloration.<P>- Chris<P>------------------<BR>--<BR>**Turbine Entertainment Software has no idea I said any of this, so don't blame them.<p>[This message has been edited by Stormwaltz (edited 08-05-1999).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Baphomet</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I must really be missing a lot from not playing Beta...determing monsters' origins, and what not. Now I am really getting impatient.<P>------------------<BR>Memory, prophecy and fantasy<BR>the past, the future and the dreaming moment between<BR>are all one country, living one immortal day. To know that is Wisdom. To use it is the Art.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ping Lo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Well, if drudges, mosswarts, banderlings and tumeroks aren't from the same world... you might want to have MS update their site to indicate otherwise.<BR> <A HREF="http://www.microsoft.com/games/zone/asheronscall/monsters.htm" TARGET=_blank>http://www.microsoft.com/games/zone/asheronscall/monsters.htm</A> </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ethos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Not sure where anyone disagreed with you on that?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ping Lo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Stormwaltz did up above.  (Which strikes me as pretty odd)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Nayt al-Yad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Aye, but perhaps I have a reason for his statement for Chris/Stormwaltz has had his first article of monster history published, which, while disagrees with Microsofts other history (see Ping Lo's link for that) on the relationship between Tumeroks and the other three races from that distant land, it is a good piece.<BR>He's titled it <A HREF="http://www.zone.com/asheronscall/ASHEdrudges.asp" TARGET=_blank>On Drudges</A> and is good work and a great read.  But Ping Lo is correct, the forces of the Empire of Gates, and the Wizards of the Turbine Fellowship must keep each other in check lest the lessons learned in history are but only rumors instead of facts.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Nayt al-Yad<BR>-----------<BR>Success is measured not in gold but in the friends at thy funeral<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Stormwaltz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Sorry for the long absence, folks. It's been the usual brushfires around here.<P>Nayt, the problem with the the inconsistency lay in Turbine's own specs, and I just happened to fall victim to it. There is a Monsters-General doc which gives a small amount of information on each species in Dereth. This doc mentions in a single sentence that Banderlings, Mosswarts, Drudges, and, yes, Tumeroks, all come from the same world.<P>On the other hand, there is the Tumerok-Dungeons doc, which goes into considerable detail about those critters, and which says absolutely nothing about the other species they supposedly share a homeworld with. It also says, "The Tumerok homeworld was dry and barren... The predominant colour of the vegetation there was mottled violet, which explains the creatures' garish coloration." If this is true, it makes no sense to think that green, swamp-dwelling Mosswarts also originate from this barren, purple world.<P>For what it's worth, which probably isn't that much, my original title for "On Drudges" was "The Nocturnes." Fortunately, they didn't change any of the text, just the title.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>- Chris<P>------------------<BR>--<BR>**Turbine Entertainment Software has no idea I said any of this, so don't blame them.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
